summary: Speculation/Theorization about Spider-Man: Far From Home
body:
Speculation/Theorization about Spider-Man: Far From Home

The role of the mentor character to replace Iron Man (because Marvel has suggested that even if Tony survives he won’t have a big role in FFH) will probably/should be be handed off to Hank Pym and Janet Van Dyne as a duo. Think about it:

- Both have experience in superheroism. Janet even basically sacrificed her life for the fate of the world. (even if she made it out alive, she had accepted she may never come back from the Quantum Realm) So upon finding out about their exploits, as well as them being SHIELD-level scientists, he’ll probably look up to them big time.

- Hank is implied to be retired, and he and Jan will likely want to make up for the missing 30 years. A romantic tour through Europe would be a good place to start, and would let them be in Europe at the same time as Peter for a reason that doesn’t seem way too convenient.

- Hank left SHIELD in a bitter rage, but Jan likely still thinks highly of them. If Fury/Hill asked her to do something as simple as keep an eye on Peter while she’s in the city, she’d probably do it, and Hank would begrudgingly take the task on to make his wife happy.

If this turns out to be true, a few things I want to see happen:

- Hank being a grumpy boi because he finds Peter irritatingly energetic and child-like, but growing to respect and even like him.

- Janet referencing the entire fandom and their exepctations with one simple line: “Henry, he’s so cute, can we adopt him?”

- Hank’s reaction to the above (“Janet I have to deal with Scott every day, don’t add on to that. Please.”)

- Mid-Credits scene: Hank and Janet are waiting at the airport. Suddenly, a van pulls up to the curb, and Hope gets out, welcoming them back home. She asks them how the trip went, Janet responds “It was lovely,” and Hank responds, “It was hell, but at least I got to be with your mother the whole way through,” and the two kiss. Hope then interjects, “If that’s the way the trip went, this will be a good bookend for both of you, since Mom will live it, and Dad,” she sheepishly flashes her hand, revealing a ring. Hank and Janet realise what that means, and Hank yells, “GOD DAMMIT SCOTT!”

summary: Who would win in a fight between the guy who shot Batman's parents and the guy who shot Uncle Ben
question: Who would win in a fight between the guy who shot Batman's parents and the guy who shot Uncle Ben
answer: One was a dude who freaked out sneaking into an old couple’s home and was arrested later that night (even if he happened to have a very unusual pursuer, but the cops had already cornered him). Joe Chill on the other hand had the guts to stick up the richest, most famous people in Gotham in what was then a well-to-do neighborhood and managed to get a pair of shots off as Thomas Wayne was charging him - Thomas Wayne who has frequently been written as single-handedly taking down the Lex Moxon gang. Chill, easy.
